A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 State Government – Grants and Contracts – Reimbursement of Indirect Costs
3 FOR the purpose of altering the rate at which certain nonprofit organizations receiving
4 State–funded grants or contracts may be reimbursed for indirect costs; and generally
5 relating to State–funded grants and contracts.
6 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
7 Article – State Finance and Procurement
8 Section 2–208
9 Annotated Code of Maryland
10 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
11 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
12 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
13 Article – State Finance and Procurement
14 2–208.
15 (a) (1) In this section the following words have the meanings indicated.
16 (2) “Indirect costs” means any costs that would be considered to be indirect
17 costs under OMB Uniform Guidance.
18 (3) “Nonprofit organization” means an organization that is tax exempt
19 under § 501(c)(3), (4), or (6) of the Internal Revenue Code.
20 (4) “OMB Uniform Guidance” means the Uniform Administrative
21 Requirements, Cost Principles, and Audit Requirements for Federal Awards adopted by the
