3 (b) (1) This section applies only to:
4 (i) a grant or contract awarded on or after October 1, 2018;
5 (ii) a multi–year grant or contract awarded before October 1, 2018,
6 if:
7 1. the grant or contract continues to be in effect on or after
8 October 1, 2018; and
9 2. funding for the grant or contract is required to be
10 authorized separately for each fiscal year; and
11 (iii) an extension or a renewal of a grant or contract if the extension
12 or renewal is awarded on or after July 1, 2019.
13 (2) This section applies whether or not the funds awarded through the
14 grant or contract are transferred directly by the State or through a third party to the
15 nonprofit organization.
16 (3) This section does not require the reimbursement of indirect costs
17 incurred under a multi–year grant or contract described under paragraph (1)(ii) of this
18 subsection during any fiscal year that begins before July 1, 2019.
19 (c) If a nonprofit organization is a direct recipient or subrecipient of a grant or
20 contract for the provision of services that is funded wholly with State funds or with a
21 combination of State and other nonfederal funds, the terms of the grant or contract shall
22 allow for reimbursement of indirect costs:
23 (1) at the same rate the nonprofit organization has negotiated and
24 received:
25 (i) for indirect costs under a direct federal award; or
26 (ii) from a nonfederal entity based on the cost principles in Subpart
27 E of OMB Uniform Guidance; or
28 (2) if the nonprofit organization has not negotiated and received an indirect
29 cost rate described in item (1) of this subsection, at a rate [of at least 10%] EQUAL TO THE
30 DE MINIMIS RATE ESTABLISHED IN SUBPART E OF OMB UNIFORM GUIDANCE of the
31 costs that would be considered modified total direct costs under OMB Uniform Guidance.
32 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
33 October 1, 2025.

